{
  "doc_id": "15659",
  "text": "where Θ(τ, z) is a suitable theta function which is Γ 0 (N )-invariant in z and transforms like a modular form of weight 3/2 (for the Kudla-Millson lift) or weight 1/2 (for the the Millson lift) for the representationρ in τ . We remark that we renormalize the Millson theta lift from [CITATION_1] by multiplication with i/ √ N to simplify the formulas. The most important properties of the two theta lifts are studied in [CITATION_2] and [CITATION_3] . It turns out that both lifts map modular functions for Γ 0 (N ) to harmonic Maass forms forρ whose ξ-images are linear combinations of unary theta functions. Further, the Fourier expansions of the holomorphic parts of the lifts are given by traces of F . We state simplified Fourier expansions of the lifts for special inputs F in Theorem 4.3.",
